The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 27 August is 2,932 (339.4 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 23 August, there were 59 new confirmed cases (6.8 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 16 August, there were 33 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 79% (26 extra cases).
